The Senate caucus of the All Progressives Congress will tomorrow meet with the Mai Mala Buni-led Caretaker Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee by 4pm. The notice of the meeting was conveyed in a letter read by the Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, moments before the chamber adjourned sitting on Wednesday. The letter was signed by the Senate Leader, Yahaya Abdullahi (APC, Kebbi North). The meeting, which was supposed to hold on Tuesday at the National Assembly, is now slated to hold tomorrow at the National Secretariat of the All Progressives Congress (APC). Lawan said, â€œThere will be APC Senate caucus meeting with the CECPC at the National Headquarters on Thursday, March 24, 2022.